{"id":437,"createdAt":"2022-11-18T18:47:31.172Z","updatedAt":"2023-08-09T16:17:11.816Z","displayColor":"#574cfa","published":true,"publishedAt":"2023-08-09T16:17:11.000Z","publishedWhere":"ResearchEquals","originMetadata":"ResearchEquals","url":"https://doi.org/10.53962/q2za-3hkc","isbn":null,"prefix":"10.53962","suffix":"q2za-3hkc","title":"Next steps in automated handler-free behavioural recordings: spatially discretized behavioural cycles","description":"Open source electronics, code and mechanical devices have enabled a proliferation of automated behavioural recordings which greatly assist neuroscience research. This is particularly important for studying prey species like the mouse, as handler-free measurement of exploitation behaviours will likely capture a different behavioural regime than traditional assays due to the lack of threatening stimuli. Following up on recent discussions of ethological neuroscience, three principles of automated maze development are outlined here, which have helped us to spatially discretize behavioural cycles in a naturalistic way.","language":"en","licenseId":1,"moduleTypeId":1,"main":{"name":"idea 1 discretized behavioural cycle recording.docx","size":168386,"uuid":"730e3536-6219-439f-b631-70f1cd7b8ced","cdnUrl":"https://ucarecdn.com/730e3536-6219-439f-b631-70f1cd7b8ced/","isImage":false,"isStored":true,"metadata":{},"mimeType":"application/vnd.openxmlformats-officedocument.wordprocessingml.document","sourceInfo":{"file":{},"source":"local"},"originalUrl":"https://ucarecdn.com/730e3536-6219-439f-b631-70f1cd7b8ced/","cdnUrlModifiers":null,"originalImageInfo":null,"originalVideoInfo":null,"originalContentInfo":{"mime":{"mime":"application/vnd.openxmlformats-officedocument.wordprocessingml.document","type":"application","subtype":"vnd.openxmlformats-officedocument.wordprocessingml.document"}}},"supporting":{"files":[]},"authorsRaw":{},"referencesRaw":{},"references":[],"authors":[{"id":342,"createdAt":"2022-11-18T18:47:31.172Z","updatedAt":"2023-08-09T13:18:13.767Z","moduleId":437,"workspaceId":7,"acceptedInvitation":true,"readyToPublish":false,"authorshipRank":0,"workspace":{"id":7,"createdAt":"2022-02-01T09:22:31.096Z","updatedAt":"2023-08-10T13:09:35.003Z","workspaceType":"Individual","handle":"maheshkarnani","avatar":"https://ucarecdn.com/5f36c8bd-7dc3-4857-8273-19a032f94a13/-/crop/268x268/0,36/-/preview/","firstName":"Mahesh","lastName":"Karnani","name":null,"bio":"Assistant Prof and group leader at VU CNCR Amsterdam. Studying neuronal control of motivated behaviours like feeding.","pronouns":"he/him","url":"https://inf.cncr.nl/research_teams/neural_circuits_of_drive/","orcid":"0000-0002-4810-4146"}}],"license":{"id":1,"createdAt":"2022-01-31T18:58:51.475Z","source":"ResearchEquals","url":"https://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/legalcode","name":"CC0 Public Domain Dedication","price":0,"price_id":null,"prod_id":"prod_M0VJdtMgxTMRvS"},"type":{"id":1,"createdAt":"2022-01-31T18:58:51.460Z","originType":"ResearchEquals","wikidata":"Q131841","name":"Idea","schema":"CreativeWork"},"parents":[],"children":[{"id":752,"createdAt":"2023-05-24T21:17:31.679Z","updatedAt":"2023-09-13T11:43:10.433Z","displayColor":"#059669","published":true,"publishedAt":"2023-08-10T13:26:20.000Z","publishedWhere":"ResearchEquals","originMetadata":"ResearchEquals","url":"https://doi.org/10.53962/mn5r-7ekh","isbn":null,"prefix":"10.53962","suffix":"mn5r-7ekh","title":"Build instructions for a long term behavioural enclosure for measuring motivational switching in mice","description":"Switching between motivated behaviours, such as feeding, drinking and socializing,  is important for survival in a dynamic, social environment. Inflexible repetitive behaviours are a hallmark of many neuropsychiatric disorders. Studies of the neural mechanisms underlying motivated behaviours, i.e., drives, seldom focus on switching between them. This is partly due to a lack of appropriate behavioural measurement systems. In this study, we build and test a device for measuring motivational switching in mice, the Switchmaze. We present build instructions using affordable off-the-shelf components, and openly accessible acquisition and analysis scripts.","language":"en","licenseId":1,"moduleTypeId":12,"main":{"name":"build instructions for a long term behavioural enclosure for measuring motivational switching in mice.pdf","size":2379943,"uuid":"4a65df40-7a37-49ca-92c6-95060ecb402a","cdnUrl":"https://ucarecdn.com/4a65df40-7a37-49ca-92c6-95060ecb402a/","isImage":false,"isStored":true,"metadata":{},"mimeType":"application/pdf","sourceInfo":{"file":{},"source":"local"},"originalUrl":"https://ucarecdn.com/4a65df40-7a37-49ca-92c6-95060ecb402a/","cdnUrlModifiers":null,"originalImageInfo":null,"originalVideoInfo":null,"originalContentInfo":{"mime":{"mime":"application/pdf","type":"application","subtype":"pdf"}}},"supporting":{"files":[{"url":"https://api.uploadcare.com/files/8e75b187-0c1e-48c0-a9aa-dbe8551211e6/","size":10347,"uuid":"8e75b187-0c1e-48c0-a9aa-dbe8551211e6","source":null,"is_image":false,"is_ready":true,"mime_type":"application/octet-stream","image_info":null,"datetime_stored":"2023-06-29T16:39:14.000733Z","default_effects":"","datetime_removed":null,"datetime_uploaded":"2023-06-29T16:39:13.900784Z","original_file_url":"https://ucarecdn.com/0876808e-30b1-42e4-8f00-48a317f21b03/Switch_maze_arduino_mega.ino","original_filename":"Switch_maze_arduino_mega.ino"},{"url":"https://api.uploadcare.com/files/bc32ede7-2bd4-4e8e-89dc-6e2672762275/","size":410,"uuid":"bc32ede7-2bd4-4e8e-89dc-6e2672762275","source":null,"is_image":false,"is_ready":true,"mime_type":"application/json","image_info":null,"datetime_stored":"2023-06-29T16:45:22.978598Z","default_effects":"","datetime_removed":null,"datetime_uploaded":"2023-06-29T16:45:22.907710Z","original_file_url":"https://ucarecdn.com/bc32ede7-2bd4-4e8e-89dc-6e2672762275/oauth2_creds.json","original_filename":"oauth2_creds.json"},{"url":"https://api.uploa